  "text": "For CSA assessment we used the calculated T1-weighted images after contrast adjustment within snap-ITK [CITATION_1] . Delineation of spinal cord was performed by outlining the spinal cord circumference manually (AH) at the C2/3 level slice by slice in the axial plane yielding a total of 15 continuous slices. For an approximation of the mean crosssectional area of the upper spinal cord the average of these 15 slices was used.",
